        </div>

        <div class="info-callout">
          <p><strong>Compare to 2025:</strong> Under 2025 rates, the same filer with the same income would pay the same 15% on the full $28,000 gain — the 0% threshold in 2025 is $48,350 for single filers, and $55,000 already exceeds it. The 2026 threshold is projected at ~$49,500, which still doesn't help this filer. However, a filer with $48,500 of ordinary income would save ~$150 in 2026 vs. 2025 on the same gain, as a larger portion falls in the 0% bracket.</p>
        </div>
